Steps to Set Up and Run Your Project with Live Server
Set Up Your Project

Create a New Folder: Create a new folder for your project, for example, my_project.
Create index.html and index.js: Inside the my_project folder, create two files: index.html and index.js.
Create HTML and JavaScript Files

index.html:


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Live Server Example</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Hello, World!</h1>
    <script src="index.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
index.js:

    console.log("Hello");

Open Your Project in VS Code

Open VS Code: Launch Visual Studio Code.
Open the Project Folder: Go to File > Open Folder... and select your my_project folder.
Install Live Server Extension

Install Live Server: Go to the Extensions view by clicking the Extensions icon in the Activity Bar on the side of the window. Search for Live Server and install the extension by Ritwick Dey.
Run the Live Server

Open index.html: In the Explorer view, locate and right-click on index.html.
Open with Live Server: Select Open with Live Server from the context menu.
View Your Project in the Browser

Your default web browser should open and display the content of index.html.
You should see "Hello, World!" on the page.
You should see a console message saying "JavaScript is running!" and an alert saying "Hello from index.js".



                 OR - Run JS in local

JS runs on browser
To run outside of browser 
1. install node
2. create a file with .js extention e.g, first.js
3. Run the code using node first.js